A Box-Behnken design was used to determine the influence of CCI, MOI, and TOH on each evaluated response. These variables were screened at a low (− 1), medium (0), and high level (+ 1) as indicated in Table 1. The different levels were linearly related for CCI and TOH and exponentially for MOI, always in an equidistant manner. The results obtained for each response were fitted to a second-order polynomial by the least squares method (Eq. 3):3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
